I suspect there are another 35 - 40 K miles left in that engine if you
change the oil faithfully as you say. Just replace the front seal, put in a
new clutch disc, clean up the pressure plate and flywheel, and feel good,
knowing you've saved plenty of money, and have another 2-4 years to save up
for when that engine has 100-120 K miles and gets tired. :-)  
Regards,
Courtney

 
